olive oil
1 cucumber
1 bunch baby broccoli
2 clove garlic
1 packet Beef Rump
1 sachet Classic Roast Seasoning
15 g butter
1 packet Mixed Salad Leaves
drizzle vinegar (balsamic or white wine)
1 packet balsamic glaze
1 packet diced bacon

• See 'Top Steak Tips!' (below left).
• Preheat BBQ to high heat.
• Slice cucumber into half-moons.
• Trim baby broccoli.
• Finely chop garlic.
• In a medium bowl, combine baby broccoli, a drizzle of olive oil and a pinch of salt and pepper.

• In a medium bowl, combine beef, Aussie spice blend and a drizzle of olive oil.

• When BBQ is hot, grill baby broccoli and diced bacon, tossing occasionally, 4-6 minutes.

No BBQ? Heat a large frying pan over a medium-high heat with a drizzle of olive oil. Cook baby broccoli and diced bacon, tossing, 6-8 minutes.

• Meanwhile, grill beef rump, turning, for 6-10 minutes for medium-rare or until cooked to your liking. Transfer to a plate and leave to rest for 5 minutes

No BBQ? In a large frying pan, heat a drizzle of olive oil over high heat. When oil is hot, cook beef rump, turning, for 5-9 minutes for medium-rare or until cooked to your liking.

• Place garlic, the butter and a pinch of salt in a small bowl, then microwave in 10 seconds bursts until melted.
• Roughly chop baby broccoli.
• In a large bowl, combine baby broccoli, bacon, melted garlic butter, mixed salad leaves, cucumber and a drizzle of vinegar and olive oil. Toss to combine. Season to taste.

• Slice beef.
• Divide spiced beef rump and charred baby broccoli-bacon salad between plates.
• Drizzle over balsamic glaze to serve. Enjoy!